AudioManagerJS
==============

A JavaScript library that easily allows the playing of audio clips from binary strings.


Usage
-------------

Its very simple to add AudioManagerJS to your web application and load a map of notes.

```javascript
var audioManagerJS = new AudioManagerJS();

var notesToLoad = {
  "A0": "data:audio/ogg;base64,",
  "A1": "data:audio/ogg;base64,",
  "A2": "data:audio/ogg;base64,"
};

audioManagerJS.loadNotes(notesToLoad, function() {
  console.log("Loading Complete!");
})
```

Once AudioManagerJS has completed loading notes it will callback to the function you pass in.

After this you are able to easily play notes using the playNote function.

```javascript
audioManager.playNote("A0");
```

It is as simple as that!
